<sn><md>## Atmospheric Nitrogen

A significant amount of $N_2$ is `fixed` in the atmoshpere by ==lightning process== (provides high energy to dissociate stable $N_2$ molecule)

Nitrogen is ==not readily dissociated by UV== in the **thermosphere** like oxygen,but at altitude ==above 100km==,atmoic nitrogen is produced by the photochemical reactions

$$ N_2 + h\nu \to N + N $$

In the troposphere ==oxides of nitrogen==(pollutant) like $NO_2$ **readily dissociate** photochemically into `NO` and reactive `atmoic oxygen`.

$$ NO_2 + h\nu \to NO + O $$

It is a significant photochemical process involved in the ==photochemical smog formation==.</md></sn><sn><md>## Atmospheric Water

Water vapor absorbs ==infrared (IR) radiation== strongly and thus,influences the earths heat balance.

Under certain circumstances,atmosphere water vapor influences the ==formation of pollution-induce fog== and also participates in different chemical process.

In **stratosphere**,the main `source of water vapor` is from the ==photochemical oxidation of methane==

$$ CH_4 + 2O_2 + h\nu \to CO_2 + 2H_2O $$

Thus,the water produced in stratorsphere serves as a ==source of hydroxyl radical== ($H\mathrm{O\cdot}$)

$$ H_2O + hv \to H\mathrm{O\cdot} + H $$</md></sn>